NNOOTTEESS
       The procedure to find the "edges" in the image is as follows:

               The Fourier transform of the image is taken,

               The  Fourier  transform  of  the Laplacian of a two-dimensional
              Gaussian function is used to filter the transformed image,

               The result is run through an inverse Fourier transform,

               The resulting image is traversed in search of places where  the
              image changes from positive to negative or from negative to pos-
              itive,

               Each cell in the map where  the  value  crosses  zero  (with  a
              change  in  value greater than the threshold value) is marked as
              an edge and an orientation is assigned  to  it.   The  resulting
              raster map layer is output.


